    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This FD3S RX-7 represents a rare, preserved example of Mazda\u2019s sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW engineering. The rotary powerplant maintains factory-spec compression, with the complex vacuum-actuated boost control system functioning flawlessly through the transition. Its lightweight chassis retains the original double-wishbone suspension geometry, providing telepathic turn-in. The drivetrain features a crisp five-speed manual transmission paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Finished in its original paint with zero oxidation, this unit shows no signs of the typical heat-cycling wear on the interior plastics or engine harness. A true collector-grade specimen that delivers the raw, analog feedback of a golden-era JDM legend.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
